{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.10",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 10 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:1",
      "text": "“I loathe my life; I will give free utterance to my complaint; I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:2",
      "text": "I will say to God, Do not condemn me; let me know why thou dost contend against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:3",
      "text": "Does it seem good to thee to oppress, to despise the work of thy hands and favor the designs of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:4",
      "text": "Hast thou eyes of flesh? Dost thou see as man sees?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:5",
      "text": "Are thy days as the days of man, or thy years as man's years,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:6",
      "text": "that thou dost seek out my iniquity and search for my sin,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:7",
      "text": "although thou knowest that I am not guilty, and there is none to deliver out of thy hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:8",
      "text": "Thy hands fashioned and made me; and now thou dost turn about and destroy me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:9",
      "text": "Remember that thou hast made me of clay; and wilt thou turn me to dust again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:10",
      "text": "Didst thou not pour me out like milk and curdle me like cheese?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:11",
      "text": "Thou didst clothe me with skin and flesh, and knit me together with bones and sinews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:12",
      "text": "Thou hast granted me life and steadfast love; and thy care has preserved my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:13",
      "text": "Yet these things thou didst hide in thy heart; I know that this was thy purpose.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:14",
      "text": "If I sin, thou dost mark me, and dost not acquit me of my iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:15",
      "text": "If I am wicked, woe to me! If I am righteous, I cannot lift up my head, for I am filled with disgrace and look upon my affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:16",
      "text": "And if I lift myself up, thou dost hunt me like a lion, and again work wonders against me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:17",
      "text": "thou dost renew thy witnesses against me, and increase thy vexation toward me; thou dost bring fresh hosts against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:18",
      "text": "“Why didst thou bring me forth from the womb? Would that I had died before any eye had seen me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:19",
      "text": "and were as though I had not been, carried from the womb to the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:20",
      "text": "Are not the days of my life few? Let me alone, that I may find a little comfort",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:21",
      "text": "before I go whence I shall not return, to the land of gloom and deep darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.10.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:22",
      "text": "the land of gloom and chaos, where light is as darkness.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
